notes: Note that birds described in this study are not complete bird community; in another paper (linked below) he cites 36 sp. in juniper site (other paper does not describe ponderosa site). Richness at each vert strata inferred from occurence figures for each species: if >3% of observations within a strata, species considered present at that strata. Species occurences within each strata were then summed to obtain estimate of richness for each strata. Bird observation methods are available in Balda 1970, which report surveys for juniper site but not ponderosa site; sampling effort for ponderosa site assumed approx. equal to his other sites: https://www.jstor.org/stable/pdf/1366011.pdf?refreqid=excelsior%3A2d15429156da6d756ae42ceb1dcf04f4
